# 🏛️ Dice of Dionysus - Cursor AI Context Rules

## Project Overview
language: JavaScript (ES6+)
type: Vanilla JS Web Game (SPA)
theme: Greek mythology-themed dice strategy game
inspiration: Balatro's design philosophy
framework: None (intentionally vanilla)
buildTool: Vite
deployment: Web + PWA + Electron

## Core Philosophy
- **Simplicity First**: Vanilla JS, no framework overhead - keep it debuggable
- **Performance Target**: 60fps gameplay, minimal bundle size
- **Modularity**: Clear separation of concerns (classes, config, data, ui, utils)
- **Maintainability**: Well-documented, consistent patterns
- **Thematic Consistency**: Greek mythology naming throughout

## Critical Rules - NEVER VIOLATE

### 1. Terminology (Memory ID: 5924352, 5376805, 5065254)
- ❌ NEVER use "houseRules" or "offerings" 
- ✅ ALWAYS use "libations" for consumable cards
- ❌ NEVER introduce new game terms without asking for thematic translation first
- ✅ Use established terms: Boons (jokers), Worship cards, Pips, Favour, Ante

### 2. Code Style
- ✅ Keep JavaScript simple and easy to debug
- ❌ NEVER add TypeScript unless explicitly requested
- ✅ Prefer existing patterns over "modern" refactors
- ❌ NEVER restructure working code without clear performance gain
- ✅ Use the Logger system instead of console.log
- ❌ NEVER remove Greek mythology theming

### 3. Architecture Preservation
- ✅ Respect class-based inheritance (Card → Joker/WorshipCard/LibationCard)
- ✅ Keep GameEngine as single source of truth for state
- ✅ Use existing config constants (GameConstants, ScoringConstants, UIConstants)
- ❌ NEVER introduce new frameworks or build systems
- ❌ NEVER split modules without explicit request

### 4. Testing & Debugging
- ✅ Debug in browser console using window.game, window.app
- ❌ NEVER create separate test files unless explicitly requested
- ✅ Use Logger.debug() for development logging
- ✅ Test in the actual game window

## Project Structure

```
DICE-OF-DIONYSUS-WORKING/
├── index.html              # Entry point
├── js/
│   ├── Main.js            # Application controller
│   ├── classes/           # Game entities (Card, Die, Joker, etc.)
│   ├── config/            # Constants (GameConstants, ScoringConstants, UIConstants)
│   ├── data/              # Game content (gameData.js, AnteData_js.js)
│   ├── game/              # Core logic (GameEngine.js - 2020 lines)
│   ├── ui/                # Rendering (UIManager.js - 1900 lines)
│   └── utils/             # Helpers (seededRNG, dataManager, Logger)
├── css/
│   ├── styles.css         # Main styles
│   └── balatro-effects.css # Visual effects
└── ART/                   # Assets (images, music)
```

## Key Systems

### 1. GameEngine (js/game/GameEngine.js)
**What it does**: Single source of truth for game state
**Key methods**: rollDice(), calculateScore(), confirmScore(), applyJokerEffects()
**State management**: All game data in this.state object
**When to edit**: Game logic, scoring, progression, card effects

### 2. UIManager (js/ui/UIManager.js)
**What it does**: All rendering and UI interactions
**Key methods**: renderDice(), updateScorecard(), openShop(), renderCard()
**Note**: Currently 1900 lines - DO NOT split unless explicitly requested
**When to edit**: Visual changes, shop, animations, user interactions

### 3. Card System (Inheritance)
```
Card.js (base class)
  ├─ Joker.js (Boons - passive effects with timing)
  ├─ WorshipCard.js (Favour boosters)
  └─ LibationCard.js (Consumables)
```

### 4. Die System (js/classes/Die.js)
**Face-specific enhancements**: Each die has 6 faces with individual enhancements
**Enhancement types**: Parchment, Iron, Gold, Mirror, Wild, Mother of Pearl
**Key feature**: faces[1-6] object with value, enhancements Set, modifiedValue

### 5. Data Management
**gameData.js**: All card definitions (boons, worship, libations, artifacts)
**AnteData_js.js**: Progression, score thresholds, boss blinds
**dataManager.js**: Save/load to localStorage

## AI Optimization Guidelines

### When Optimizing Code
✅ **DO:**
- Profile before optimizing (use browser DevTools)
- Optimize hot loops (rollDice, calculateScore, rendering)
- Cache calculations where safe
- Use existing patterns (seededRNG for randomness)
- Preserve game balance constants in config/

❌ **DON'T:**
- Introduce new dependencies
- Change architecture without benchmarking
- Optimize prematurely
- Break deterministic seeded RNG
- Change game balance without permission

### When Adding Features
✅ **DO:**
- Add new boons to gameData.js → implement in Joker.js applyTimingEffect()
- Add new libations to gameData.js → implement in LibationCard.js applyLibationEffect()
- Use existing timing system (before_roll, before_score, after_score, etc.)
- Follow Greek mythology theming
- Add to card_database.csv for documentation

❌ **DON'T:**
- Create new card types without asking
- Introduce new game mechanics without thematic names
- Break existing card interactions
- Ignore rarity system (rustic, vibrant, epic, worship, libation)

### When Fixing Bugs
✅ **DO:**
- Use Logger.error() to log issues
- Check BUGS_FIXED_LOG.md for previous fixes
- Test with deterministic seeds
- Verify save/load compatibility
- Update CHANGELOG.md

❌ **DON'T:**
- Make defensive changes that hide root cause
- Break backwards compatibility with saves
- Remove error handling to "clean up code"

## Code Patterns to Follow

### 1. Logging (NEW in Phase 3)
```javascript
// Use Logger, not console.log
Logger.debug('Dice rolled', { faces: [1,2,3,4,5] });
Logger.info('Ante started', { ante: 2 });
Logger.warn('Low gold warning', { gold: 1 });
Logger.error('Save failed', error);
```

### 2. Configuration Constants
```javascript
// Use constants from config/, don't hardcode
GAME_BALANCE.STARTING_GOLD  // ✅
SCORING.YAHTZEE_BASE        // ✅
15                          // ❌
```

### 3. Card Effects (Timing-based)
```javascript
// Jokers use timing system
timing: { 
    before_roll: true,     // Before dice roll
    before_score: true,    // Before scoring
    after_score: true,     // After scoring
    turn_start: true,      // Start of turn
    turn_end: true         // End of turn
}
```

### 4. Seeded RNG
```javascript
// ALWAYS use this.prng, NEVER Math.random()
this.prng.random()           // ✅ Returns 0-1
this.prng.randomInt(1, 6)    // ✅ Returns 1-6
Math.random()                // ❌ Breaks determinism
```

## Performance Targets
- **Bundle size**: ~120KB total
- **Frame rate**: 60fps during gameplay
- **Load time**: <2s on modern browsers
- **Memory**: Minimal allocations in game loop

## Common AI Tasks

### "Add a new boon"
1. Define in gameData.js (jokers array)
2. Implement effect in Joker.js applyTimingEffect() switch
3. Add to assetMapping.js if custom image
4. Test with seed for reproducibility

### "Optimize performance"
1. Profile with Chrome DevTools first
2. Focus on: rollDice(), calculateScore(), rendering loops
3. Cache where safe, pool objects if needed
4. Verify determinism still works

### "Fix a bug"
1. Reproduce with specific seed
2. Check BUGS_FIXED_LOG.md for similar issues
3. Use Logger to trace issue
4. Fix root cause, not symptom
5. Update CHANGELOG.md

### "Add UI feature"
1. Edit UIManager.js (keep existing structure)
2. Use balatro-effects.css for animations
3. Maintain responsive design
4. Test on mobile viewport

## GitHub Integration Notes
- Main branch: production-ready code
- Commit messages: Follow conventional commits
- PRs: Include testing steps with seed
- Issues: Reference BUGS_FIXED_LOG.md for context

